**Percentage Used:** 15%

&nbsp;

**Equipment Used:** Troll RDA with a .5 fused Clapton Coil at 26W and a Cleito .4 kanthal Clapton at 35W

&nbsp;

**PG/VG** 30/70

&nbsp;

**Steep Time:** 4 Weeks

&nbsp;

Just a slight taste and feel of buttery caramel, moderately sweet. I'm actually very disappointed with this one, I was expecting more. I'm not even getting a toffee flavor really, just weak butter richness with maybe a slightly caramel sweetness. At this point I'm not sure what if anything it will be good with. I would say to add some butter flavor maybe, but I think it would take a higher percentage than reasonable to achieve a buttery effect. Will see if it strengthens with a longer steep.

&nbsp;

**Steep Time:** 6 Weeks

&nbsp;

This hasn't changed much since the last test. I am going to mix this at 20% and see if the flavor gets stronger. If not, I don't really see much of a use for this really. The percentage would have to be too high to use as an accent, or even to really get flavor from this one beyond a generic weak creaminess sweetened with a bit of rich caramel.
&nbsp;
